Based on user information and analytics from LinkedIn, develop two
distinct customer-avatar personas (buyer personas) that will later review
the user's LinkedIn posts before publication.

These two personas must be distinct from each other (different age range,
seniority, company size, industry within the audience spectrum, mindset)
but both must be plausible representatives of the actual follower base.

# Output rules — read carefully

Produce EXACTLY two blocks in the format below — nothing else. No
introduction, no commentary, no headers other than "PERSONA 1" / "PERSONA 2".

The text inside <Role> must contain ONLY the character description (who
this person IS — age, role, seniority, company context, personality,
pressures, what they value, what they distrust). 4–6 sentences, written
in 2nd-person addressing the persona.

**Start every <Role> block with "Du bist …"** (German) or "You are …"
(English). Example:
"Du bist eine 45-jährige Geschäftsführerin eines mittelständischen
IT-Beratungshauses in München. Du hast 15+ Jahre Berufserfahrung in
digitaler Transformation. Du bist pragmatisch, ergebnisorientiert und
skeptisch gegenüber Hype-Themen."

DO NOT include any feedback-task instructions ("Your goal is to act as a
representative…", "you evaluate campaigns…", etc.) in the output.
Those task instructions live in a separate downstream template — adding
them here would cause duplication.

DO NOT use "Act as", "Agiere als", "Ich bin", "Stell dir vor" or similar
prefixes. The role block IS the persona, not a description of someone
playing them.

Write in the same language as the audience description below (German if
that is German).

# Format

###
PERSONA 1
<Role>
Du bist [4–6-sätzige Charakterbeschreibung — Alter, Rolle,
Senioritätslevel, Branchenkontext, Persönlichkeit, Druckpunkte. KEINE
Aufgaben-Beschreibung.]
</Role>

<Organization>
[Eine 2–3-sätzige Beschreibung der Firma dieser Persona: Größe, Branche,
Geschäftsmodell, Umsatzklasse falls relevant, aktuelle Challenges —
abgeleitet aus den Analytics.]
</Organization>

PERSONA 2
<Role>
[Distinct profile, gleiche Struktur]
</Role>

<Organization>
[Distinct profile, gleiche Struktur]
</Organization>
